<p>
	Save that masterpiece with the filename of <code>MySuperBlog.html</code> (note the <code>.html</code>
	extension in the name&mdash;that's very important!).
</p>
<p>
	Now open up your new <code>MySuperBlog.html</code> file in your browser. Double-clicking on the file in
	Explorer or Finder should work in most cases. You can also drag the file from Finder/Explorer
	into your browser window to open it. Or if all else fails you can type the file's location into your
	browser's address bar. For example, if you saved your file at <code>C:\MySuperBlog.html</code>, you could type
	<code>C:\MySuperBlog.html</code> into your browser then hit Enter or Return on your keyboard and you should
	see your page.
</p>
<p>
	Once you've done that, you should be looking at a page in your browser that looks something like this:
</p>
